str2: Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.

str2: From sun and ago; to lead together, i.e. Collect or convene; specially, to entertain.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To fill, load. Transitive from gemo; to fill entirely.
Twelve; the usual way in which the Twelve apostles of Jesus are referred to. From duo and deka; two and ten, i.e. A dozen.
A large basket. Of uncertain derivation; a basket.
A fragment, broken piece. From klao; a piece.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Made of barley. From krithe; consisting of barley.
Bread, a loaf, food. From airo; bread or a loaf.

str2: From perissos; to superabound, be in excess, be superfluous; also to cause to superabound or excel.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

str2: To eat. A reduplicated and prolonged form of an obsolete primary verb; to eat.
